{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1054,"text":"Some months back,\nI was visiting this East African city,"},{"time":6558,"text":"and we were stuck in traffic."},{"time":9571,"text":"And this vendor suddenly\napproaches my window"},{"time":12637,"text":"with a half-opened alphabet sheet."},{"time":16505,"text":"I took a quick look at the alphabet sheet,"},{"time":19348,"text":"and I thought of my daughter,"},{"time":20807,"text":"how it would be nice\nto spread it on the floor"},{"time":23393,"text":"and just play all over it with her"},{"time":25257,"text":"while getting her to learn the alphabet."},{"time":27470,"text":"So the traffic moved a bit,\nand I quickly grabbed a copy,"},{"time":30789,"text":"and we moved on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34165,"text":"When I had time to fully open\nthe alphabet sheet"},{"time":37290,"text":"and take a more detailed look at it,"},{"time":39643,"text":"I knew I was not going to use that\nto teach my daughter."},{"time":43267,"text":"I regretted my purchase."},{"time":46331,"text":"Why so?"},{"time":48338,"text":"Looking at the alphabet sheet\nreminded me of the fact"},{"time":51148,"text":"that not much has changed"},{"time":53548,"text":"in the education curricula in Africa."},{"time":56729,"text":"Some decades back, I was taught\nout of a similar alphabet sheet."},{"time":61312,"text":"And because of that,\nI struggled for years."},{"time":64464,"text":"I struggled to reconcile my reality\nwith the formal education I received"},{"time":68984,"text":"in school, in the schools I attended."},{"time":72592,"text":"I had identity crises."},{"time":74626,"text":"I looked down on my reality."},{"time":77559,"text":"I looked at my ancestry,\nI looked at my lineage with disrespect."},{"time":82205,"text":"I had very little patience\nfor what my life had to offer around me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89045,"text":"Why?"},{"time":91496,"text":"\"A is for apple.\""},{"time":94421,"text":"\"A is for apple.\""},{"time":97528,"text":"\"A is for apple\" is for that child\nin that part of the world"},{"time":102240,"text":"where apples grow out;"},{"time":104751,"text":"who has an apple in her lunch bag;"},{"time":108235,"text":"who goes to the grocery store\nwith her mom and sees red,"},{"time":111661,"text":"green, yellow -- apples\nof all shapes and colors and sizes."},{"time":116049,"text":"And so, introducing\neducation to this child"},{"time":118962,"text":"with an alphabet sheet like this"},{"time":122090,"text":"fulfills one of the major\nfunctions of education,"},{"time":125155,"text":"which is to introduce the learner"},{"time":128341,"text":"to an appreciation\nof the learner's environment"},{"time":131738,"text":"and a curiosity to explore more\nin order to add value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137581,"text":"In my own case,"},{"time":140014,"text":"when and where I grew up in Africa,"},{"time":143613,"text":"apple was an exotic fruit."},{"time":146719,"text":"Two or three times a year,"},{"time":148128,"text":"I could get some yellowish apples\nwith brown dots, you know,"},{"time":153519,"text":"signifying thousands of miles traveled --\nwarehouses storing --"},{"time":157440,"text":"to get to me."},{"time":159575,"text":"I grew up in the city"},{"time":161510,"text":"to very financially comfortable parents,"},{"time":164534,"text":"so it was my dignified reality,"},{"time":166500,"text":"exactly the same way"},{"time":168835,"text":"cassava fufu or ugali\nwould not regularly feature"},{"time":173021,"text":"in an American, Chinese or Indian diet,"},{"time":176851,"text":"apples didn't count as part of my reality."},{"time":180208,"text":"So what this did to me,"},{"time":183280,"text":"introducing education to me\nwith \"A is for apple,\""},{"time":186988,"text":"made education an abstraction."},{"time":189914,"text":"It made it something out of my reach --"},{"time":192665,"text":"a foreign concept,"},{"time":194595,"text":"a phenomenon for which I would have\nto constantly and perpetually seek"},{"time":198425,"text":"the validation of those it belonged to"},{"time":200260,"text":"for me to make progress\nwithin it and with it."},{"time":204109,"text":"That was tough for a child;\nit would be tough for anyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208042,"text":"As I grew up and I advanced academically,"},{"time":210789,"text":"my reality was further separated\nfrom my education."},{"time":216739,"text":"In history, I was taught"},{"time":218509,"text":"that the Scottish explorer Mungo Park\ndiscovered the Niger River."},{"time":223631,"text":"And so it bothered me."},{"time":225448,"text":"My great-great-grandparents grew up"},{"time":227487,"text":"quite close to the edge\nof the Niger River."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229514,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":231957,"text":"And it took someone to travel\nthousands of miles from Europe"},{"time":238458,"text":"to discover a river\nright under their nose?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":240929,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243394,"text":"No!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244575,"text":"(Applause and cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":250018,"text":"What did they do with their time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":251971,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":253892,"text":"Playing board games, roasting fresh yams,"},{"time":256747,"text":"fighting tribal wars?"},{"time":258557,"text":"I mean, I just knew my education\nwas preparing me to go somewhere else"},{"time":263441,"text":"and practice and give to another\nenvironment that it belonged to."},{"time":267232,"text":"It was not for my environment,\nwhere and when I grew up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271029,"text":"And this continued."},{"time":272212,"text":"This philosophy undergirded my studies"},{"time":274129,"text":"all through the time I studied in Africa."},{"time":276618,"text":"It took a lot of experiences\nand some studies"},{"time":280476,"text":"for me to begin to have\na change of mindset."},{"time":283652,"text":"I will share a couple\nof the remarkable ones with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287735,"text":"I was in the United States\nin Washington, DC"},{"time":290114,"text":"studying towards my doctorate,"},{"time":292180,"text":"and I got this consultancy position\nwith the World Bank Africa Region."},{"time":296735,"text":"And so I remember one day,"},{"time":299515,"text":"my boss -- we were having\na conversation on some project,"},{"time":304187,"text":"and he mentioned a particular\nWorld Bank project,"},{"time":307252,"text":"a large-scale irrigation project\nthat cost millions of dollars"},{"time":312248,"text":"in Niger Republic"},{"time":313603,"text":"that was faltering sustainably."},{"time":316901,"text":"He said this project\nwasn't so sustainable,"},{"time":319268,"text":"and it bothered those\nthat instituted the whole package."},{"time":324035,"text":"But then he mentioned\na particular project,"},{"time":327517,"text":"a particular traditional irrigation method\nthat was hugely successful"},{"time":332458,"text":"in the same Niger Republic\nwhere the World Bank project was failing."},{"time":336930,"text":"And that got me thinking."},{"time":339281,"text":"So I did further research,"},{"time":341984,"text":"and I found out about Tassa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345775,"text":"Tassa is a traditional irrigation method"},{"time":349569,"text":"where 20- to 30-centimeter-wide\nand 20- to 30-centimeter-deep holes"},{"time":355786,"text":"are dug across a field to be cultivated."},{"time":359220,"text":"Then, a small dam is constructed\naround the field,"},{"time":364296,"text":"and then crops are planted\nacross the surface area."},{"time":367946,"text":"What happens is that when rain falls,"},{"time":371274,"text":"the holes are able to store the water"},{"time":374282,"text":"and appropriate it to the extent\nthat the plant needs the water."},{"time":378124,"text":"The plant can only assimilate\nas much water as needed"},{"time":381414,"text":"until harvest time."},{"time":384582,"text":"Niger is 75 percent scorched desert,"},{"time":388299,"text":"so this is something\nthat is a life-or-death situation,"},{"time":391016,"text":"and it has been used for centuries."},{"time":393384,"text":"In an experiment that was conducted,"},{"time":396233,"text":"two similar plots of land\nwere used in the experiment,"},{"time":401670,"text":"and one plot of land"},{"time":404325,"text":"did not have the Tassa technique on it."},{"time":406291,"text":"Similar plots."},{"time":407482,"text":"The other one had Tassa technique\nconstructed on it."},{"time":411332,"text":"Then similar grains of millet\nalso were planted on both plots."},{"time":416045,"text":"During harvest time,"},{"time":418276,"text":"the plot of land without Tassa technique"},{"time":421452,"text":"yielded 11 kilograms\nof millet per hectare."},{"time":426737,"text":"The plot of land with Tassa technique"},{"time":429056,"text":"yielded 553 kilograms\nof millet per hectare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435660,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":438269,"text":"I looked at the research,\nand I looked at myself."},{"time":442206,"text":"I said, \"I studied\nagriculture for 12 years,"},{"time":445482,"text":"from primary to Senior Six,\nas we say in East Africa,"},{"time":448916,"text":"SS3 in West Africa or 12th grade."},{"time":451286,"text":"No one ever taught me"},{"time":452967,"text":"of any form of traditional\nAfrican knowledge of cultivation --"},{"time":456797,"text":"of harvesting, of anything --"},{"time":458615,"text":"that will work in modern times\nand actually succeed,"},{"time":462467,"text":"where something imported from the West\nwould struggle to succeed."},{"time":467775,"text":"That was when I knew the challenge,"},{"time":470912,"text":"the challenge of Africa's curricula,"},{"time":473649,"text":"And I thus began my quest\nto dedicate my life, concern my life work,"},{"time":478471,"text":"to studying, conducting research\non Africa's own knowledge system"},{"time":482787,"text":"and being able to advocate\nfor its mainstreaming"},{"time":485811,"text":"in education, in research, policy"},{"time":488682,"text":"across sectors and industries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491445,"text":"Another conversation\nand experience I had at the bank"},{"time":495313,"text":"I guess made me take that final decision\nof where I was going to go,"},{"time":500087,"text":"even though it wasn't the most lucrative\nresearch to go into,"},{"time":504135,"text":"but it was just about what I believed in."},{"time":506937,"text":"And so one day, my boss said\nthat he likes to go to Africa"},{"time":511587,"text":"to negotiate World Bank loans\nand to work on World Bank projects."},{"time":516614,"text":"And I was intrigued. I asked him why."},{"time":518587,"text":"He said, \"Oh, when I go to Africa,"},{"time":521057,"text":"it's so easy."},{"time":523255,"text":"I just write up my loan documents\nand my project proposal in Washington, DC,"},{"time":527937,"text":"I go to Africa, and they all\njust get signed."},{"time":530914,"text":"I get the best deal, and I'm back to base."},{"time":534326,"text":"My bosses are happy with me.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":536933,"text":"But then he said,\n\"I hate going to Asia or ...\""},{"time":540644,"text":"and he mentioned a particular country,\nAsia and some of these countries."},{"time":544111,"text":"\"They keep me for this, trying\nto get the best deal for their countries."},{"time":548158,"text":"They get the best deal."},{"time":549358,"text":"They tell me, 'Oh,\nthat clause will not work for us"},{"time":552290,"text":"in our environment."},{"time":553921,"text":"It's not our reality.\nIt's just so Western.'"},{"time":556918,"text":"And they tell me, 'Oh,\nwe have enough experts"},{"time":560053,"text":"to take care of this."},{"time":561280,"text":"You don't have enough experts."},{"time":562925,"text":"We know our aim.'"},{"time":564102,"text":"And they just keep going\nthrough all these things."},{"time":566571,"text":"By the time they finish,\nyes, they get the best deal,"},{"time":569115,"text":"but I'm so exhausted and I don't get\nthe best deal for the bank,"},{"time":572304,"text":"and we're in business.\""},{"time":573507,"text":"\"Really?\" I thought in my head, \"OK.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":575326,"text":"I was privileged to sit in on\na loan negotiating session"},{"time":579630,"text":"in an African country."},{"time":581319,"text":"So I would do these consultancy\npositions during summer,"},{"time":584163,"text":"you know, since I was a doctoral student."},{"time":586871,"text":"And then I traveled with the team,\nwith the World Bank team,"},{"time":591227,"text":"as more like someone to help out\nwith organizational matters."},{"time":595567,"text":"But I sat in during\nthe negotiating session."},{"time":599730,"text":"I had mostly Euro-Americans, you know,\nwith me from Washington, DC."},{"time":604686,"text":"And I looked across the table\nat my African brothers and sisters."},{"time":609993,"text":"I could see intimidation on their faces."},{"time":612771,"text":"They didn't believe\nthey had anything to offer"},{"time":615058,"text":"the great-great-grandchildren\nof Mungo Park --"},{"time":617370,"text":"the owners of \"apple\" in \"A is for apple.\""},{"time":620011,"text":"They just sat and watched:\n\"Oh, just give us, let us sign."},{"time":622811,"text":"You own the knowledge. You know it all."},{"time":624748,"text":"Just, where do we sign?\nShow us, let us sign.\""},{"time":626981,"text":"They had no voice.\nThey didn't believe in themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634544,"text":"Excuse me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636587,"text":"And so,"},{"time":639212,"text":"I have been doing this for a decade."},{"time":641562,"text":"I have been conducting research\non Africa's knowledge system,"},{"time":645030,"text":"original, authentic,\ntraditional knowledge."},{"time":647298,"text":"In the few cases where this\nhas been implemented in Africa,"},{"time":650519,"text":"there has been remarkable\nsuccesses recorded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653027,"text":"I think of Gacaca."},{"time":655256,"text":"Gacaca is Rwanda's traditional\njudicial system"},{"time":660012,"text":"that was used after the genocide."},{"time":662130,"text":"In 1994, when the genocide ended,"},{"time":666100,"text":"Rwanda's national court system\nwas in shambles:"},{"time":668686,"text":"no judges, no lawyers to try\nhundreds of thousands of genocide cases."},{"time":674236,"text":"So the government of Rwanda\ncame up with this idea"},{"time":677768,"text":"to resuscitate a traditional\njudicial system known as Gacaca."},{"time":681625,"text":"Gacaca is a community-based\njudicial system,"},{"time":685096,"text":"where community members come together"},{"time":688057,"text":"to elect men and women of proven integrity"},{"time":691830,"text":"to try cases of crimes committed\nwithin these communities."},{"time":697255,"text":"So by the time Gacaca concluded\nits trial of genocide cases in 2012,"},{"time":703619,"text":"12,000 community-based courts\nhad tried approximately 1.2 million cases."},{"time":711334,"text":"That's a record."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713169,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":718438,"text":"Most importantly is that Gacaca emphasized\nRwanda's traditional philosophy"},{"time":724062,"text":"of reconciliation and reintegration,"},{"time":727179,"text":"as against the whole\npunitive and banishment idea"},{"time":731081,"text":"that undergirds present-day Western style."},{"time":735481,"text":"And not to compare, but just to say\nthat it really emphasized"},{"time":739400,"text":"Rwanda's traditional method of philosophy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743269,"text":"And so it was Mwalimu Julius Nyerere,"},{"time":745890,"text":"former president of Tanzania --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":747655,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":749155,"text":"who said that you cannot develop people."},{"time":752916,"text":"People will have to develop themselves."},{"time":756563,"text":"I agree with Mwalimu."},{"time":758487,"text":"I am convinced"},{"time":759899,"text":"that Africa's further transformation,\nAfrica's advancement,"},{"time":763546,"text":"rests simply in the acknowledgment,\nvalidation and mainstreaming"},{"time":768349,"text":"of Africa's own traditional, authentic,\noriginal, indigenous knowledge"},{"time":773362,"text":"in education, in research,\nin policy making and across sectors."},{"time":778816,"text":"This is not going to be easy for Africa."},{"time":781357,"text":"It is not going to be easy for a people\nused to being told how to think,"},{"time":784845,"text":"what to do, how to go about it,"},{"time":787234,"text":"a people long subjected\nto the intellectual guidance"},{"time":790412,"text":"and direction of others,"},{"time":792178,"text":"be they the colonial masters,"},{"time":793869,"text":"aid industry or international news media."},{"time":796865,"text":"But it is a task that we have to do\nto make progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800123,"text":"I am strengthened by the words\nof Joseph Shabalala,"},{"time":803047,"text":"founder of the South African choral group\nLadysmith Black Mambazo."},{"time":806545,"text":"He said that the task ahead of us\ncan never, ever be greater"},{"time":812256,"text":"than the power within us."},{"time":814433,"text":"We can do it."},{"time":815615,"text":"We can unlearn looking down on ourselves."},{"time":818199,"text":"We can learn to place value\non our reality and our knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822418,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823597,"text":"(Swahili) Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825092,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":826639,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828865,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}